<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20202] Test failure: org.apache.cassandra.transport.SimpleClientPerfTest</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20202</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SimpleClient uses a CQLMessageHandler instance to deal with response messages in the V5 framing format. It looks like &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16663&quot; title=&quot;Request-Based Native Transport Rate-Limiting&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16663&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16663&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; broke SimpleClient&apos;s ability to return capacity allocated during the processing of inbound messages (i.e. responses from server-&amp;gt;client) back to the global and per-endpoint resource monitors. The change in behaviour introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20052&quot; title=&quot;Size of CQL messages is not limited in V5 protocol logic&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20052&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20052&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, in which we now push back to the client when a capacity for a large message can&apos;t be allocated, causes SimpleClientPerfTest in the burn suite to fail on V5/V6. This is purely because the test expects the client to run for a fixed period without interruption, but now it halts as soon as capacity is exhausted. The simple fix is to restore SimpleClient&apos;s capacity return.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
