                            <comment id="17913003" author="beobal" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 17:49:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As seen in: &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-4.1/542/#showFailuresLink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-4.1/542/#showFailuresLink&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17913005" author="beobal" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 17:55:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dnk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dnk&quot;&gt;dnk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17913010" author="dnk" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 18:15:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=samt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;samt&quot;&gt;samt&lt;/a&gt;, thank you for highlighting the issue, I am trying to reproduce it locally and understand the root cause better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17913080" author="dnk" created="Tue, 14 Jan 2025 21:49:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prior the suggested fix SimpleClient overrode method org.apache.cassandra.transport.CQLMessageHandler#processRequest(Envelope request) to intercept the moment when a response was fully received and processed to release capacity but it was not invoked by CQLMessageHandler (after changes done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16663&quot; title=&quot;Request-Based Native Transport Rate-Limiting&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16663&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16663&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). CQLMessageHandler invokes processRequest(Envelope request, Overload backpressure). So, org.apache.cassandra.net.AbstractMessageHandler#releaseCapacity was not invoked for the responses within the SimpleClient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So when we executed the test endpointReserveCapacity/globalReserveCapacity were leaking and &quot;using&quot; Limit value reached the limit value.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13073997/13073997_client_capacity_leak_before.png&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prior to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20052&quot; title=&quot;Size of CQL messages is not limited in V5 protocol logic&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20052&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20052&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; CQLMessageHandler and correspondently SimpleClient ignored the capacity leaking by allowing to process messages even if there is no available capacity in endpointReserveCapacity/globalReserveCapacity, as a result it masked the issue with leaking.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20052&quot; title=&quot;Size of CQL messages is not limited in V5 protocol logic&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20052&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20052&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; CQLMessageHandler has started to really apply backpressure by treating lack of capacity as a signal to pause messages receiving. So, in case of SimpleClient we stuck in responses receiving due to lack of free capacity.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13073999/13073999_lack_of_client_capacity_moment.png&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the current ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=samt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;samt&quot;&gt;samt&lt;/a&gt; has fixed the SimpleClient logic is used to intercept CQLMessageHandler response processing, so there is no the capacity leak anymore.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13073998/13073998_client_capacity_after.png&quot; width=&quot;400&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The mentioned tests are failed on my laptop as well before the fix and are passing after applying the suggested change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The suggested change looks good to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
